          <p id="IO-PB.800">UN political missions and peacebuilding operations work in the field to prevent and resolve conflicts or to promote enduring peace in post-conflict societies. They are supported by the Department of Political and Peacebuilding Affairs (DPPA), which was established on 1 January 2019. The Department assists envoys and advisers bearing the UN Secretary-General’s `good offices’ for the resolution of conflicts or implementation of other UN mandates.</p>
          <p usage="edio">The DPPA’s Mediation Support Unit (MSU), supports the mediation capacity of regional organizations; provides logistical, advisory and financial support to peace processes; and collates knowledge on policy and best practices.</p>
          <p usage="ewyb edio">
      An intergovernmental advisory 
      <xr pageref="N" ref="IO-UNGA.789">Peacebuilding Commission,</xr>
       a special subsidiary body of both the UN Security Council and General Assembly, was inaugurated in June 2006. A multi-year standing Peacebuilding Fund, established in October 2009, finances—through an Immediate Response Facility and the Peacebuilding Recovery Facility—the implementation of initiatives in countries that are on the agenda of the Peacebuilding Commission, or that have been declared eligible for assistance by the UN Secretary-General. A Peacebuilding Support Office was established within the UN 
      <xr pageref="N" ref="IO-UN.334">Secretariat</xr>
       to administer the fund, as well as to assist the Commission. The Office was incorporated into the DPPA in 2019.
    </p>
          <p usage="ewyb edio sasia">The UN Assistance Mission in Afghanistan is directed by the Department of Peace Operations.</p>
